gomodel:SYNGO_3728  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0030285 replaced by GO:0030672" , "Rationale: Figure 7: highly purified synaptic vesicles obtained by controlled pore-glass chromatography showed that SVOP proteins are highly enriched in synaptic vesicles (similar as the homologous SV2 proteins)\n\nFigure 8: immunoprecipitations of synaptic vesicles from brain homogenates with beads coated with antibodies to synaptotagmin and synaptobrevin showed SVOP co-immunoprecipitation\n\n19/6/2018 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: M&M: RAT brain fractionations were performed essentially as described by Huttner et al. (1983)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9900-4233" ;
